==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''femina'': woman  + ''sole'': alone.

===Noun===
{{en-noun2|'''feme sole'''|'''femes sole'''}}

#{{Law}} A single woman, whether [[unmarried]], [[spinster]], [[widow]] or [[divorcee]].
#*"To Mary Smith an adult '''feme sole''', you are hereby summonsed...."

